id: pm-ts-starter-41z0
title: Reported extension version drifts from released version (hardcoded VERSION constant)
description: "Found during 2026-06-12 fleet verification vs CLI 2026.6.12 (companion task pm-cli-website-z50w): published pm-ts-starter 2026.6.10 reports version 2026.6.4 in 'pm ts-starter info' and extension metadata. Cause: const VERSION = \"2026.6.4\" hardcoded in index.ts — the Daily Release workflow auto-bumps package.json/manifest.json and only rewrites 'version: \"...\"' literals (single match), so a bare constant silently drifts. Fix: resolve VERSION from manifest.json at module load (dist/../manifest.json), with 0.0.0 fallback; test now asserts against manifest.json instead of a snapshot literal."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[2]: bug,release-automation
created_at: "2026-06-12T23:04:53.761Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-12T23:04:54.577Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: pm ts-starter info reports the same version as manifest.json/package.json in every future release without manual edits
files[2]{path,scope,note}:
  index.ts,project,VERSION resolved from manifest.json at load
  test/smoke.test.ts,project,assert version against manifest.json
close_reason: "Fixed: VERSION read from manifest.json; functionally verified via pm extension --install in throwaway workspace (info now reports 2026.6.9 = manifest); tests 2/2 pass"
body: ""
